quran[14]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,105,"“Were not My signs{1}recited to you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>, but you used to disbelieve them?”",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used isayat(singularayah). Ayahmeans ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an,like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose.Each such unit isconsidered a ‘sign’from God.
  23,106,"They said{1}, “Our Lord, our wretchedness overcame us, and we were a people astray.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  23,107,"Our Lord, bring us out of this, and if we ever return, we would truly be unjust.”"
  23,108,"He said, “Be despised<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>therein and do not speak to Me."
  23,109,"Indeed, there was a group of My servants who used to say, ‘Our Lord, we have attained faith, so forgive us and have mercy on us, and You are the best of the merciful.’"
  23,110,"But you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>made them a target of ridicule until they made you forget My remembrance, and you used to laugh at them."
  23,111,"Today I have indeed rewarded them for what they endured patiently<span class=""h"">, for</span>it<sup foot_note=""80643"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup>is they who are the triumphant ones.”"
  23,112,"<span class=""h"">He said<sup foot_note=""80644"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, “How long did you remain on earth in terms of number of years?”"
  23,113,"They said, “We remained a day or part of a day, so ask those who keep count.”"
  23,114,"<span class=""h"">He said<sup foot_note=""80645"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, “You<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>remained but for a little while, if you only knew."
  23,115,"Did you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>think that We had created you in vain, and that to Us <span class=""h"">you would not be returned<sup foot_note=""80646"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>?”"
  23,116,"Rather, Most High is Allah, the True King; there is no god but He, the Lord of the Noble Throne."
  23,117,"And whoever calls upon another god with Allah—he has no proof thereof—his reckoning rests with his Lord; indeed, the deniers never succeed."
  23,118,"And say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “My Lord, forgive and have mercy, for You are the best of the merciful.”"
